<subSubSection id="C375A0EEFFE2375B8EAEFC06FA59FBB4" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD0F365FFE2375B8EAEFC06FA59FBB4" blockId="10.[151,1436,475,1082]" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B91B2F77FFE2375B8EAEFC06FEE1FC6A" bold="true" box="[199,315,947,971]" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is the largest member of the genus. The male resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F88E6FFE2375B8A61FC06FB5CFC6A" box="[1032,1158,947,971]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Catalina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variolus">
<emphasis id="B91B2F77FFE2375B8A61FC06FB5CFC6A" box="[1032,1158,947,971]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">C. variolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., in shape of thecal processes) but is more robust, with longer ventral theca processes and a much larger apical process of the style; the female differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F88E6FFE2375B8F1EFC4BFE25FBB7" box="[375,511,1022,1046]" class="Insecta" family="Aphrophoridae" genus="Aphrophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="siccifolia">
<emphasis id="B91B2F77FFE2375B8F1EFC4BFE25FBB7" box="[375,511,1022,1046]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">C. siccifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in both size and steepness of the pronotum, which in this specimen exceeds 
<number id="3DA7E142FFE2375B8B3EFC48FAA9FBB4" box="[1367,1395,1021,1045]" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" value="45.0">45</number>
o.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C375A0EEFFE2375B8EAEFB97FD5FFB98" box="[199,645,1057,1082]" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" type="etymology">
